# Database and Options Safety

- Use WordPress APIs (`get_option`, meta APIs, settings APIs) before custom SQL.
- For custom SQL, use `$wpdb->prepare()` and explicit column allowlists.
- Make schema/setup routines idempotent and safe to run multiple times.
- Never run destructive data operations without guards and capability checks.
- Add sensible defaults and validate option values before persisting.
- Keep data migrations reversible when feasible and log migration intent.
- Index frequently filtered columns in custom tables.
- Avoid storing large transient or cache blobs in autoloaded options.
